18 January 2010Government Communication and Information System (GCIS) will launch the South African chapter of the Southern African Development Community (SADC) Media Awards Competition.The 2010 theme for the awards is, Promoting Regional Integration through Excellent Journalism . The categories for the awards are Print, Radio, Television and PhotojournalismThe details are as follows:Date: 28 January 2010Time: 18h00Venue: to be confirmedThe South African chapter of the awards competition was launched during November 2003 and GCIS is the contact point for South African media and the SADC Secretariat.South African journalists have previously been named as winners of the television category in 2006 and the radio category in 2006 and 2009.It is anticipated that the 2010 SADC media awards will take place in June 2010To RSVP contact: Takalani Mashamba at 012 314 2416/078 252 3722For enquiries contact:Bongiwe Gambu (Pretoria) Tel: 012 314 2148 Cell: 082 714 9463Colin Cruywagen (Cape Town) Cell: 082 377 9916Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)